<zk>
	<vlayout>
		<label value="ZK-5992 — tbeditor plugin loading (scope resolution)"/>
		<label multiline="true">
What this page shows: how the plugin set is resolved across scopes
(closest scope wins; an empty value clears) and that a bad name is tolerated.

How to verify (browser developer tools → Network / Console):
1. tbColors: per-component plugins="colors,fontsize" → loads colors.js + fontsize.js.
2. tbInherited (no plugins=): inherits "emoji" from the window custom-attribute → loads emoji.js.
3. tbOverride (plugins="colors"): OVERRIDES the inherited emoji → loads colors only, NOT emoji.
4. tbClear (plugins=""): explicitly clears → loads no plugin at all.
5. tbUnknown (plugins="z_does_not_exist"): the missing plugin asset fails to load
   gracefully — its request 503s during the page-load burst (404 on an isolated
   fetch) — but the editor and page still work.
   ONE console error for z_does_not_exist is EXPECTED here (unknown-plugin tolerance).
		</label>

		<!-- AC1: per-component attribute -->
		<tbeditor id="tbColors" plugins="colors,fontsize" width="500px"/>

		<!-- AC4: custom-attribute walks up the component tree -->
		<window id="winInherit" border="normal">
			<custom-attributes org.zkoss.zkmax.zul.tbeditor.plugins="emoji"/>

			<!-- inherits emoji from window's custom-attribute -->
			<tbeditor id="tbInherited" width="500px"/>

			<!-- AC3 (override): own plugins= REPLACES the inherited custom-attribute
				(no merge) — resolves to colors only, not colors+emoji. colors is also
				requested by tbColors above, so it dedupes to a single load (AC6). -->
			<tbeditor id="tbOverride" plugins="colors" width="500px"/>

			<!-- AC3 (override to none): an explicit empty plugins= clears the inherited
				'emoji' for this editor — resolves to no plugins. -->
			<tbeditor id="tbClear" plugins="" width="500px"/>
		</window>

		<!-- AC5: unknown plugin name should not crash editor or page render. -->
		<tbeditor id="tbUnknown" plugins="z_does_not_exist" width="500px"/>
	</vlayout>
</zk>
